{
  "objective": "Create a closed self-calibrating ZPD learning loop by (1) adding a persistent FrontierManager that tracks solved/unsolved skill boundaries per domain and supports sampling near that frontier, (2) extending QuestionGenerator with a new 'frontier' source so the system can ask why boundary problems are hard, and (3) updating CurriculumGenerator to preferentially draw a fixed portion of each batch from frontier-sampled problems (slightly harder than current mastery). This makes problem difficulty selection autonomous and continuously self-correcting as competence changes.",
  "files": {
    "python/sare/memory/frontier_manager.py": "Implement the full FrontierManager module as specified: ProblemStatus enum; FrontierProblem and DomainStats dataclasses; ring-buffer-like eviction via max_size; persistence to data/memory/frontier.jsonl; APIs: add_pending(), record(), sample_near_frontier(), domain_stats(), get_unsolved_frontier(), get_difficulty_distribution(); singleton acce

{
  "objective": "Wire curriculum selection to live learning state by making ProblemGenerator and DevelopmentalCurriculum competence-aware, generating Zone-of-Proximal-Development (ZPD) problems for weak-but-reachable domains and using current competence/prerequisites to adapt difficulty and domain unlocking dynamically.",
  "files": {
    "problem_generator.py": "1) Extend ProblemGenerator.generate_batch(...) and generate_for_domain(...) to use competence-aware ZPD targeting consistently: accept domain_competence (dict domain->competence) and optional target_difficulty; restrict sampling to domains whose competence is in the optimal learning band (0.3-0.7) while excluding mastered domains (>0.85) and optionally excluding too-weak domains (<0.2) except as part of prerequisite recovery. 2) Make the ZPD target difficulty dynamic: when target_difficulty is None, set target_diff = clamp(competence + margin, 0.0, 0.9) with margin tuned (e.g., +0.15..+0.25) and bias selection toward template

{
  "objective": "Add an Open-Ended ProblemGenerator that produces structurally diverse, difficulty-calibrated, cross-domain (and analogy/retretries) problems, then integrate it into the curriculum developmental pipeline without breaking public interfaces, so the learning loop closes: curriculum generation becomes novelty/surprise-driven and competence-aware.",
  "files": {
    "python/sare/curriculum/problem_generator.py": "Introduce/replace the current (fixed) generator logic with the provided Open-Ended Problem Generator design: implement ProblemGenerator with template-driven structural roles, novel-domain templates, cross-domain analogy templates, difficulty calibration using a competence map, and optional failure retries. Add methods used by the system: __init__, update_competence(domain, competence), record_failure(expr, domain), record_analogy_success(role), generate_batch(size, target_domains=None, include_failures=True, include_analogies=True) returning List[dict]/List[Generat

